      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi @patrick@stwcx.xyz\nThanks for your reply.\nI agree that renaming would have a significant impact — it touches all repos using this interface, involves multiple owners, and requires their help to update and verify.\n\nFor context, the original Item.Dram proposal was based on Ed Tanous\u0027s discussion in https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/87221/comment/f2d528d4_a14a51b0/ about the conceptual difference between DIMM and DRAM.\n\nHowever, I noticed that Item.Dimm already includes HBM/HBM2/HBM3 in its DeviceType enum (https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/Dimm.interface.yaml#L214-L222). Would it be appropriate to use Item.Dimm directly for GPU embedded memory (HBM)? Because rename could potentially have a very large impact.Thanks.",
